                        "content": "During the assessment, what is the nurse's primary goal for a confused and disoriented client diagnosed with post-traumatic stress disorder?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIt is important to make a confused client feel safe. Explaining the unit rules and orienting the client to the unit are part of any admission process. Stabilizing psychiatric needs is a long-term goal.\n\nClient Needs: Safe and Effective Care Environment\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Implementation\nPriority Concepts: Mood and Affect, Safety\nStrategies: Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs Theory, Strategic Words\n\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, primary. Focus on the information provided in the question, and use Maslow's Hierarchy of Needs theory. Remember that when a physiological need does not exist, safety needs take precedence next.",
                        "id": "180b7518102344db8eca3c9d15951d54",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
