                        "content": "Which piece of subjective data obtained during assessment of a severely anxious client would indicate the possibility of posttraumatic stress disorder?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nIn post-traumatic stress disorder, the client relives the traumatic experience. Only the correct option includes the defining characteristic symptom of post-traumatic stress disorder. Fear of going outside is characteristic of a phobia, while always crying may indicate depression. Excessive handwashing is a characteristic of obsessive-compulsive disorder.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Recognize Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Anxiety, Interpersonal Violence\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the defining characteristics of post-traumatic stress disorder. Think about the characteristics of this disorder to assist in directing you to the correct option.\n ",
