                        "content": "A client is diagnosed with rape trauma syndrome. The nurse plans care based on which syndrome-associated fact?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe major trauma of rape or sexual assault involves the victim's emotional reaction to being physically forced to do something against their will. The life-threatening nature of the crime and feelings of helplessness, loss of control, and experiencing the self as an object of the perpetrator's rage combine to produce the victim's overpowering fear and stress. In this syndrome, which has been called rape trauma syndrome, the client reexperiences the trauma, as evidenced by recurrent recollections of the event. The remaining options are not associated with rape trauma syndrome.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Anxiety, Interpersonal Violence\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, rape trauma syndrome. Think about the manifestations that occur in a post-trauma event. Remembering that the client reexperiences the trauma, as evidenced by recurrent recollections of the event, will direct you to the correct option.\n ",
