                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe major clinical manifestation associated with post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is client experience of flashbacks. Flashbacks are not specifically associated with anxiety, agoraphobia, or schizophrenia.\n\nClient Needs: Psychosocial Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Analyze Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Mental Health\nHealth Problem: Mental Health: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Analysis\nPriority Concepts: Stress and Coping, Mood and Affect\nStrategies: Subject\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, a diagnosis specifically associated with flashbacks. Focus on the data provided in the question. It is necessary to know that flashbacks are specifically associated with PTSD. Flashbacks are not characteristic of the other options.\n ",
